---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 65
By: Yoka Daishi
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Separation-Sin=The Mote in the Eye
  - Combat-Action=Judgement
---
‘No’ is not necessarily ‘No’, nor is ‘Yes’ ‘Yes’;

But when you miss even a tenth of an inch, the difference widens up to one
thousand miles;

When it is ‘Yes’, a young Naga girl in an instant attains Buddhahood,

When it is ‘No’, the most learned Zensho while alive falls into hell.
